Bullets 2 and 3

library(ggplot2); library(dplyr); library(tidyverse); library(ggmosaic)
##  Attaching packages  tidyverse 1.3.0 
##  tibble  2.1.3      purrr   0.3.3
##  tidyr   1.0.2      stringr 1.4.0
##  readr   1.3.1      forcats 0.4.0
##  Conflicts  tidyverse_conflicts() 
## x tidyr::extract()   masks magrittr::extract()
## x dplyr::filter()    masks stats::filter()
## x dplyr::lag()       masks stats::lag()
## x purrr::set_names() masks magrittr::set_names()
classInterests <- read.csv("/cloud/project/homework-1-aluken95/ds4ph-bme/data/classInterests.txt", sep = "")
classInterest <- classInterests %>%
  group_by(Program, Year) %>%
  summarise(counts = n())
classInterest$Year <- factor(classInterest$Year, levels = c("Sophomore", "Junior", "Senior", "Master's", "PhD"))

#barplot
bp <- classInterest %>%
 ggplot(aes(x=Year, y=counts, fill=Program)) +
 geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = position_dodge())+
 geom_text(aes(label=counts), vjust=1.6, color = "black", position = position_dodge(0.9), size = 3.5) +
 scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Pastel2") +
 theme_minimal() +
 labs(title = "Distribution of Years and Programs in \nIntro to Data Science for Public Health")
plot(bp)

#mosaic plot
mp <-  ggplot(data = classInterest) +
 geom_mosaic(aes(x=product(Program, Year), fill=factor(Program))) +
 labs(x="Year", y="Program", title="Mosaic Plot of Program and Year of Intro to Data Science Students") +
 guides(fill=guide_legend(title = "Program"))+
 scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Pastel2") +
 theme_minimal() +
 theme(axis.text.y=element_text(angle=25, vjust=5), axis.text.x=element_text(angle=50)) #not sure how to improve the spacing on y-axis
plot(mp)

geneDat <- read.csv("/cloud/project/assignment-3-aluken95/2018/data/GSE5859_exprs.csv", header = TRUE)
geneDat <- select(geneDat, -X)
 
#subtract row means from each value
testrows <- as.data.frame(rowMeans(geneDat[1:nrow(geneDat),]))
repRow <- function(x, n) {matrix(rep(x, each=n), ncol=n, byrow=TRUE)}
rowMatrix <- repRow(rowMeans(geneDat), 208)
newRow <- geneDat-rowMatrix
 
#now subtract column averages from each value
testcols <- as.data.frame(colMeans(geneDat[, 1:ncol(geneDat)]))
repCol <- function(x, n) {matrix(rep(x, each=n), nrow=n, byrow=FALSE)}
colMatrix <- repCol(colMeans(geneDat), 8793)
final <- newRow - colMatrix

Bullets 5 and 6

library(tidyverse); library(dplyr); library(ggplot2); library(grid)
dat <- read.csv("/cloud/project/assignment-3-aluken95/healthcare-spending.csv", sep = ",", header =TRUE) #I manually deleted the first two rows and the notes at the bottom.
colnames(dat) <- c("Location", 1991:2014)
dat <- as.data.frame(dat)
dat2 <- dat %>%
 gather(Year, TotHealthSpend, -Location)
 
#generate line graph
p <- ggplot(dat2, aes(x=Year, y=TotHealthSpend, group=Location))+
 geom_line(aes(color=Location)) +
 labs(y ="Total Health Spending", title = "Total US Health Spending from 1991 to 2014 (with Overall US Spending)") +
 geom_text(data = subset(dat2, Year == "2014"), aes(label= Location, color = Location), hjust = -.1)
p
gt <- ggplotGrob(p)
gt$layout$clip[gt$layout$name == "panel"] <- "off"
grid.draw(gt)

dat_noUS <- filter(dat2, Location != "United States")

q <- ggplot(dat_noUS, aes(x=Year, y=TotHealthSpend, group=Location))+
  geom_line(aes(color=Location)) +
  labs(y ="Total Health Spending", title = "Total US Health Spending from 1991 to 2014 (without Overall US Spending)") +
  geom_text(data = subset(dat_noUS, Year == "2014"), aes(label= Location, color = Location), hjust = -.1)
q
gt <- ggplotGrob(q)
gt$layout$clip[gt$layout$name == "panel"] <- "off"
grid.draw(gt)

#Barplot
meanDat <- dat_noUS %>%
  group_by(Location) %>%
  summarise(mean = mean(TotHealthSpend))
bp <- ggplot(meanDat, aes(x=Location, y=mean)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill = "#009999") +
  theme(axis.text.x=element_text(angle=-50)) +
  labs(title = "Average State Healthcare Spending from 1991 to 2014")
bp
